  - parsing
  - language-model
  - python
abstract: >
  fastNLTK is a drop-in Rust-accelerated replacement for the Natural Language
  Toolkit (NLTK). It preserves the exact NLTK Python API while replacing hot
  paths with compiled Rust code, delivering 5–168× speed improvements across
  tokenization, tagging, stemming, parsing, metrics, language modeling, and more.
  Requires no code changes beyond changing the import statement.
